b"[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](sbe48459.htm)  [Next](sbe48461.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n13\\. Not so, on account of non-specification.\n\nNor is it true that the text 'Doing works here,' &c., is meant to divert him\nwho knows the Self from knowledge and restrict him to works. For there is no\nspecial reason to hold that that text refers to works as independent means of\na desirable result: it may as well be understood to refer to works merely\nsubordinate to knowledge. As he who knows the Self has to practise meditation\nas long as he lives, he may also have to practise, for the same period, works\nthat are helpful to meditation. Having thus refuted the objection on the\nground of the reason of the matter, the Sutrakara proceeds to give his own\ninterpretation of the text.\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: 14. Or the permission is for the purpose of\nglorification](sbe48461.htm)\n\n"